        "timestamp": "2020-03-10 15:45:28.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1\n> \n> shall we not exclude also the results included closed\n> \n> sdc-be 30205/tcp closed unknown\n> sdc-fe 30206/tcp closed unknown \n> portal-app 30213/tcp closed unknown\n> aai-modelloader 30229/tcp closed unknown\n> appc 30231/tcp closed unknown\n> sdnc 30246/tcp closed unknown\n> sdc-dcae-fe 30263/tcp closed unknown\n> sdc-dcae-dt 30265/tcp closed unknown\n\nI agree that ports recognized by nmap as closed should not be reported at all since there are no applications listening on them (https://nmap.org/book/man-port-scanning-basics.html).\n\nHaving said that I would like to double check if these are actually unnecessarily exposed from corresponding services.",
